Finally, we discuss the energy loss of Egopt − qVOC. Energy qVOC is equivalent to the splitting of the quasi-Fermi levels of holes and electrons under photoirradiation, which are related to the energy levels and the charge density at the steady state. Therefore, Egopt − qVOC includes both single-particle state energetics and the charge recombination kinetics. This kinetic loss can be described as the energy difference, ECT − qVOC. The total energy loss Egopt − qVOC is the sum of the energetics and kinetic losses58,4Egopt-qVOC=Egopt-ECT+ECT-qVOC\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$E_{\mathrm{g}}^{{\mathrm{opt}}} - qV_{{\mathrm{OC}}} = \left( {E_{\mathrm{g}}^{{\mathrm{opt}}} - E_{{\mathrm{CT}}}} \right) + \left( {E_{{\mathrm{CT}}} - qV_{{\mathrm{OC}}}} \right)$$\end{document}
